cross-functional, more rational, etcetera. In the old days, Kaiser Karl and=
 Bruno Pavlovsky, the company=E2=80=99s president of fashion, won every bat=
tle based on their gut instincts and stature. Now, as Pavlovsky approaches =
his own retirement, there=E2=80=99s an opportunity for Nair to recalibrate =
and set the company on a more modern course. There is speculation that Joyc=
e Green, who used to run the American fashion business under Pavlovsky but =
was moved to France last year, will replace him.

Hiring Blazy would be the strongest indication that Nair is looking to orga=
nize Chanel more like Herm=C3=A8s, which is happy to put its designers (and=
